                <note rend="inline" type="source">637.0023/73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-13T17:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1923—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. Colonel Tarafa today delivered consolidation bill as accepted by leaders in
                    Congress. Bill apparently carries out articles of agreement with sugar
                    companies, monopolistic features seemingly removed as well as providing for
                    non-par value shares of holding company. Tarafa states President Zayas consented
                    to Senate consideration of the bill probably beginning Tuesday 18th, and
                    indicated he would sign law if passed although he objects to importation
                    features insisted upon by the sugar companies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
